It was learnt that the duo decided to travel through Igueben to avoid the bad state of the Benin-Auchi-Okenne highway when they were reportedly attacked at Ewosa. It was also gathered that some personnel of the NSCDC have been deployed to the area. “They were on their way to Benin but because of the bad state of portions along the Auchi-Benin road, they decided to pass through Igueben to cut off the bad spots but unfortunately the incident happened around Ewossa before Ekpon”, a ‎source said.  The state Commissioner of Police, Danmallam Mohammed, while confirming the incident, said a combined operation of security agencies in the state were being put in place to apprehend the abductors.